Search Tools
========================================================

* I started with [URI Library Guide](http://uri.libguides.com/life "Life, Environment and Marine Sciences Library Guide") 
* This is the life, Environment and Marine science staging page
* Lists many useful databases that URI has subscriptions too
* Conspicuous absences are [Bioone](http://bioone.org "Research Evolved") and [Google Scholar](http://scholar.google.com/ "Stand on the shoulders of giants")

Useful Databases
=======
![alt text](logos.png)
* All easy to search have account systems to save searches, and other advanced functions
* Many smaller databases may be useful for particular topics
* Read the abstracts!
* Google Scholar very good at locating specific articles and determining URI's access to that article.
* JSTOR is a good place to look for older journal editions

